[{"categories":[],"date":"2025-09-01T16:50:23-03:00","id":"/posts/build-in-public1/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003ch2 id=\"build-in-public-1-tech-stack-decisions-for-a-fintech-startup\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  \u003cstrong\u003eBuild in Public #1: Tech Stack Decisions for a Fintech Startup\u003c/strong\u003e\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#build-in-public-1-tech-stack-decisions-for-a-fintech-startup\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"/images/nami.jpg\" alt=\"nami\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou\u0026rsquo;ll find honest analysis of each choice, performance benchmarks, financial context, detailed tradeoffs, and migration strategies. Nothing is set in stone, these are decisions for today that will evolve as we learn and grow.\u003c/p\u003e","tags":[],"title":"Build in Public 1"},{"categories":[],"date":"2025-08-05T16:54:10-03:00","id":"/posts/heap-vs-stack/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003ch3 id=\"what-is\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  \u003cstrong\u003eWhat is \u0026ldquo;The Heap\u0026rdquo;?\u003c/strong\u003e\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#what-is\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"/images/heap.jpg\" alt=\"Heap Memory Illustration\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Heap is commonly used for allocating memory for objects, arrays, and other data structures that require a flexible size during program execution. It is particularly useful in scenarios where the size of the data is not known beforehand or may change during the program\u0026rsquo;s runtime. Examples include dynamically sized arrays, linked lists, and instances of classes in object-oriented programming.\u003c/p\u003e","tags":[],"title":"Heap vs Stack"},{"categories":[],"date":"2025-07-27T16:16:31-03:00","id":"/posts/my-first-post/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003ch3 id=\"hello\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  Hello\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#hello\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u